				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">If you're really tight for RAM to the point where you can't waste a single 256-byte page, you could try wasting less than 64 nibbles. Fill a page with $FF and don't use the first byte of each 4-byte word. For example, if you need only four sprites, you can use $0200-$020F for these sprites, and then you can use $0211-$0213, $0215-$0217, $0219-$021B, ..., $02FD-$02FF for anything. You can even use the low nibble of the Y coordinate bytes ($0210, $0214, etc.) as long as the value remains within $F0-$FF to keep the unused sprite off-screen. If I remember correctly, Hot Seat Harry by Memblers uses this technique in page 0 to keep the code tiny.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

