					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">It'll be a function of the exact temperature, voltage on the +5V line, what adjacent bits had previously been set to (all of &quot;same word line&quot;, &quot;physically adjacent&quot;, and &quot;same bit line&quot;) if you aren't waiting for complete steady-state decay, and lots of other analog effects. When my NES is cold, it seems to <em>mostly</em> decay to a steady-state of almost all OAM addresses containing 0x0F, but there are at least 8 bytes of exceptions. When my NES is warm I know it does something different.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

